entry.title: In Battle for Gaza City, Israeli Military Enters Densely Populated Urban Area
entry.content: Israel began in earnest its difficult push into Gaza City, sending troops into an urban Hamas stronghold that is still packed with civilians after one of the most intense bombing barrages of the monthlong war.

entry.title: Hamas Took More Than 200 Hostages From Israel. Here's What to Know.
entry.content: Militants from the Gaza Strip abducted civilians and soldiers in the attack on Israel.

entry.title: Argentina's Next President Will Face an Economy in Crisis
entry.content: As Argentines prepare to choose a new president later this month, the once-prosperous nation is grappling with its most debilitating economic crisis in a generation.
